The '''Protected areas of Kyrgyzstan''' cover 1,476,121.6 hectares and account for 7.38% of the country's total area (2017). They include * 10 strict [[nature reserve]]s (IUCN Category I), * 13 – nature [[national park]]s (IUCN Category II), * 19 – [[natural monument]]s (IUCN Category III), * 45 – habitat/species management areas, therof ** 23 – botanical reserves, ** 8 – forest reserves, ** 12 – game (zoological) reserves, ** 2 – complex reserves) (IUCN Category IV).<ref>[http://ecology.gov.kg/page/view/id/201 State Agency on Environment Protection: Specially Protected Areas in Kyrgyzstan (in Russian)]</ref> Besides, Biosphere Territory [[Yssyk-Kel]] with a status of protected area of national significance was established in 2000.
