This is the list of the [[Star designation#Proper names|proper names for the stars]] in the [[constellation]] [[Lepus (constellation)|Lepus]]. (Used in modern Western [[astronomy]] and [[uranography]] only).
==List== {| class=wikitable ! [[star]] !! proper name !! etymon |- | α Lep || Arneb || Arabic |- | || Arsh || Arabic |- | β Lep || Nihal || Arabic |}
== Etymologies ==
=== [[Alpha Leporis|α Lep]] === * '''Arneb''', Elarneb: : ＜ ([[Arabic|ar]]) ''arnab'', "[[hare]]" ＜ (sci.-ar)<ref>sci.-ar ＝ scientific Arabic. See Kunitzsch & Smart (2006) p.4.</ref> ''al-Arnab'', "[[Lepus (constellation)|the Hare]]", for the whole constellation. * '''Arsh''': : ＜ (ar) ''‘arsh'', [[throne]] ＜ (ind.-ar)<ref>ind.-ar ＝ indigenous Arabic. See ''ibid''.</ref> ''‘Arsh al-[[Orion (constellation)|Jawzā']]'', "the Throne of Jawzā'", for α, β, [[Gamma Leporis|γ]], [[Delta Leporis|δ]] [[Lepus (constellation)|Lep]].
=== [[Beta Leporis|β Lep]] === * '''Nihal''': : ＜ (ar) ''nihāl'', "quenching their thirst" ＜ (ind.-ar) ''al-Nihāl'', "(the [[Camel]]s ) Beginning to Quench Their Thirst", for α, β, γ, δ Lep.
